Definition: [ἄλλως] adverb from {{g243}}; differently
[ἀλλόφυλος] from {{g243}} and {{g5443}}; foreign, i.e. (specially) Gentile
[ἀλλότριος] from {{g243}}; another's, i.e. not one's own; by extension foreign, not akin, hostile
[ἀλλοτριεπίσκοπος] from {{g245}} and {{g1985}}; overseeing others' affairs, i.e. a meddler (specially, in Gentile customs)
[ἄλλος] a primary word; "else," i.e. different (in many applications)
[ἅλλομαι] middle voice of apparently a primary verb; to jump; figuratively, to gush
[ἀλλογενής] from {{g243}} and {{g1085}}; foreign, i.e. not a Jew
[ἀλλήλων] Genitive plural from {{g243}} reduplicated; one another
[ἄλογος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3056}}; irrational
[ἀλοάω] from the same as {{g257}}; to tread out grain
[ἀμελέω] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3199}}; to be careless of
[ἄμεμπτος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3201}}; irreproachable
[ἀμάω] from {{g260}}; properly, to collect, i.e. (by implication) reap
[ἀμέθυστος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3184}}; the "amethyst" (supposed to prevent intoxication)
[ἀμετάθετος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3346}}; unchangeable, or (neuter as abstract) unchangeability
[ἀμετακίνητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3334}}; immovable
[ἀμέμπτως] adverb from {{g273}}; faultlessly
[ἀμέριμνος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3308}}; not anxious
[ἀμεταμέλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3338}}; irrevocable
[ἀμετανόητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3340}}; unrepentant
[ἄμαχος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3163}}; peaceable
[ἁμαρτωλός] from {{g264}}; sinful, i.e. a sinner
[ἁμάρτημα] from {{g264}}; a sin (properly concrete)
[ἁμαρτάνω] perhaps from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g3313}}; properly, to miss the mark (and so not share in the prize), i.e. (figuratively) to err, especially (morally) to sin
[ἀμάρτυρος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a form of {{g3144}}; unattested
[ἁμαρτία] from {{g264}}; a sin (properly abstract)
[ἀμαθής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3129}}; ignorant
[ἅμα] a primary particle; properly, at the "same" time, but freely used as a preposition or adverb denoting close association
[ἀμάραντος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of {{g3133}}; unfading, i.e. (by implication) perpetual
[ἀμαράντινος] from {{g263}}; "amaranthine", i.e. (by implication) fadeless
[ἀλείφω] from {{g1}} (as particle of union) and the base of {{g3045}}; to oil (with perfume)
[ἀλεκτοροφωνία] from {{g220}} and {{g5456}}; cock-crow, i.e. the third night-watch
[ἄκων] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g1635}}; unwilling
[ἀλάβαστρον] neuter of ἀλάβαστρος (of uncertain derivation), the name of a stone; properly, an "alabaster" box, i.e. (by extension) a perfume vase (of any material)
[ἀλαζονεία] from {{g213}}; braggadocio, i.e. (by implication) self-confidence
[ἀλαζών] from ἄλη (vagrancy); braggart
[ἀλαλάζω] from ἀλαλή ( a shout, "halloo"); to vociferate, i.e. (by implication) to wail; figuratively, to clang
[ἀλάλητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2980}}; unspeakable
[ἄλαλος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2980}}; mute
[ἅλας] from {{g251}}; salt; figuratively, prudence
[ἀκωλύτως] adverb from a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g2967}}; in an unhindered manner, i.e. freely
[ἀκυρόω] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2964}}; to invalidate

[ἀκροβυστία] from {{g206}} and probably a modified form of πόσθη (the penis or male sexual organ); the prepuce; by implication, an uncircumcised (i.e. gentile, figuratively, unregenerate) state or person
[ἀκροατής] from ἀκροάομαι (to listen; apparently an intensive of {{g191}}); a hearer (merely)
[ἀκροατήριον] from {{g202}}; an audience-room
[Ἀκύλας] probably for Latin  (an eagle); Akulas, an Israelite
[ἄκρον] neuter of an adjective probably akin to the base of {{g188}}; the extremity
[ἀκροθίνιον] from {{g206}} and θίς (a heap); properly (in the plural) the top of the heap, i.e. (by implication) best of the booty
[ἀκρογωνιαῖος] from {{g206}} and {{g1137}}; belonging to the extreme corner
[ἀμπελών] from {{g288}}; a vineyard
[Ἀμπλίας] contracted for Latin  (enlarged); Amplias, a Roman Christian
[ἀμύνομαι] middle voice of a primary verb; to ward off (for oneself), i.e. protect
[ἀμφίβληστρον] from a compound of the base of {{g297}} and {{g906}}; a (fishing) net (as thrown about the fish)
[ἀμφιέννυμι] from the base of {{g297}} and ἕννυμι (to invest); to enrobe
[Ἀμφίπολις] from the base of {{g297}} and {{g4172}}; a city surrounded by a river; Amphipolis, a place in Macedonia
[ἄμφοδον] from the base of {{g297}} and {{g3598}}; a fork in the road
[ἀμφότερος] comparative of ἀμφί (around); (in plural) both
[ἀμώμητος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3469}}; unblamable
[ἄμωμος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3470}}; unblemished (literally or figuratively)
[ἀλλάσσω] from {{g243}}; to make different
[ἀλλαχόθεν] from {{g243}}; from elsewhere
[ἀλίσγεμα] from ἀλισγέω (to soil); (ceremonially) defilement
[ἀλλά] neuter plural of {{g243}}; properly, other things, i.e. (adverbially) contrariwise (in many relations)
[ἁλιεύω] from {{g231}}; to be a fisher, i.e. (by implication) to fish
[ἁλίζω] from {{g251}}; to salt
[ἀληθῶς] adverb from {{g227}}; truly
[ἁλιεύς] from {{g251}}; a sailor (as engaged on the salt water), i.e. (by implication) a fisher
[ἀλληγορέω] from {{g243}} and ἀγορέω (to harangue (compare {{g58}})); to allegorize
[ἀλληλουϊα] of Hebrew origin (imperative of {{h1984}} and {{h3050}}); praise ye Jah!, an adoring exclamation
[ἀμίαντος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and a derivative of {{g3392}}; unsoiled, i.e. (figuratively) pure
[ἀμήτωρ] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3384}}; motherless, i.e. of unknown maternity
[ἀμήν] of Hebrew origin ({{h543}}); properly, firm, i.e. (figuratively) trustworthy; adverbially, surely (often as interjection, so be it)
[ἄμετρος] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3358}}; immoderate
[ἀμοιβή] from ἀμείβω (to exchange); requital
[ἀμνός] apparently a primary word; a lamb
[ἄμμος] perhaps from {{g260}}; sand (as heaped on the beach)
[Ἀμιναδάβ] of Hebrew origin ({{h5992}}); Aminadab, an Israelite
[ἀμπελουργός] from {{g288}} and {{g2041}}; a vine-worker, i.e. pruner
[ἄμπελος] probably from the base of {{g297}} and that of {{g257}}; a vine (as coiling about a support)
[Ἀλεξανδρεύς] from Ἀλεξάνδρεια (the city so called); an Alexandreian or inhabitant of Alexandria
[ἀλέκτωρ] from ἀλέκω (to ward off); a cock or male fowl
[Ἀλέξανδρος] from the same as (the first part of) {{g220}} and {{g435}}; man-defender; Alexander, the name of three Israelites and one other man
[Ἀλεξανδρῖνος] from the same as {{g221}}; Alexandrine, or belonging to Alexandria
[ἀλήθεια] from {{g227}}; truth
[ἄλευρον] from ἀλέω(to grind); flour
[ἀληθής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g2990}}; true (as not concealing)
[ἀληθεύω] from {{g227}}; to be true (in doctrine and profession)
[ἀλήθω] from the same as {{g224}}; to grind
[ἀληθινός] from {{g227}}; truthful
[Ἀμών] of Hebrew origin ({{h526}}); Amon, an Israelite
[ἅλυσις] of uncertain derivation; a fetter or manacle
[ἀλυσιτελής] from {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and the base of {{g3081}}; gainless, i.e. (by implication) pernicious
[Ἀλφαῖος] of Hebrew origin (compare {{h2501}}); Alphæus, an Israelite
[ἅλων] probably from the base of {{g1507}}; a threshing-floor (as rolled hard), i.e. (figuratively) the grain (and chaff, as just threshed)
[ἀλόη] of foreign origin (compare {{g174}}); aloes (the gum)
[ἅλς] a primary word; "salt"
[ἁλυκός] from {{g251}}; briny
[ἀλυπότερος] comparative of a compound of {{g1}} (as a negative particle) and {{g3077}}; more without grief
[ἀλώπηξ] of uncertain derivation; a fox, i.e. (figuratively) a cunning person
[ἅλωσις] from a collateral form of {{g138}}; capture, be taken.
